Use this table to determine which law to use based on the given information:

{1.5}

| Given | Case | Use | Notes |
| 2 angles, 1 side | AAS/ASA | Law of Sines | Find 3rd angle first |
| 2 sides, opp.\ angle | SSA | Law of Sines | Ambiguous! 0, 1, or 2 solutions |
| 2 sides, incl.\ angle | SAS | Law of Cosines | Find 3rd side first |
| 3 sides | SSS | Law of Cosines | Find largest angle first |

**Quick mnemonic:**

- **Law of Sines:** Need an **opposite pair** (angle and its opposite side)

- **Law of Cosines:** Need an **included** setup (SAS) or all sides (SSS)

